{
  "texts": [
    "First, most of the LLMs are proprietary products made available through commercial companies such as OpenAI, Google, and Meta.",
    "While FLAN-T5 by Google and Llama2 by Meta are currently freely available or upon request, it is hard to predict whether and at what price they will charge for using their models.",
    "The rising costs of close-sourced LLMs such as GPTs also raise concerns about the feasibility of large-scale analysis of social media data.",
    "Currently, it costs $10 for 1 million tokens with GPT-4-Turbo, which is 200 times the price for GPT-3-Turbo.",
    "It is unknown whether they will continue to increase and what consequences this may have on researchers with limited financial resources."
  ]
}